PantheonOS operates under a system of non-negotiable Invariants ‚Äî foundational constraints that apply regardless of user intent, daemon state, or narrative context.
These Invariants function analogously to:
	‚Ä¢	axioms in mathematics,
	‚Ä¢	conservation laws in physics,
	‚Ä¢	kernel-level safety constraints in operating systems.

They are not advisory.
They are hard boundaries of what PantheonOS is allowed to be.

This section defines the first three categories of Invariants:
	‚Ä¢	Ethical
	‚Ä¢	Temporal
	‚Ä¢	Structural

